<p><a name="Other_places_that_use_Mifare_Technology" id="Other_places_that_use_Mifare_Technology"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=MIFARE&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Other places that use Mifare Technology">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Other places that use Mifare Technology</span></h2>
<p><b>Transportation</b></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Touch_%27n_Go" title="Touch 'n Go">Touch 'n Go</a> - uses MiFare technology (Malaysia)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Mybi" title="Mybi">Mybi</a>, <a href="/wiki/T-money" title="T-money">T-money</a>, <a href="/wiki/Upass" title="Upass" class="mw-redirect">Upass</a> also uses MiFare technology (South Korea)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Opus_card" title="Opus card" class="mw-redirect">Opus card</a> - uses Mifare technology (Canada)<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since November 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Oyster_card" title="Oyster card">Oyster card</a> - uses Mifare technology (England)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Smartrider" title="Smartrider" class="mw-redirect">Smartrider</a> - uses MIFARE technology (Australia)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Mifare4mobile" title="Mifare4mobile">Mifare4mobile</a>- MiFare in the NFC mobile services context</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/National_Tariff_System#OV-Chipkaart" title="National Tariff System">OV-Chipkaart</a> - uses MiFare technology (The Netherlands)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Charlie_Card" title="Charlie Card" class="mw-redirect">Charlie Card</a> - uses MiFare technology (Boston, USA)
<ul>
<li><i><a href="/wiki/MBTA_v._Anderson" title="MBTA v. Anderson" class="mw-redirect">MBTA v. Anderson</a></i> - Civil case related to the <a href="/wiki/Responsible_disclosure" title="Responsible disclosure" class="mw-redirect">responsible disclosure</a> of flaws in the system</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Yang_Cheng_Tong" title="Yang Cheng Tong">Yang Cheng Tong</a> - uses MiFare technology(Guangzhou,China)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Yikatong" title="Yikatong" class="mw-redirect">Yikatong</a> - uses MiFare technology (Beijing, China)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/EasyCard" title="EasyCard">EasyCard</a> - uses MiFare technology, with more than 13 million cards in circulation（Taiwan)</li>
<li><a href="/w/index.php?title=Cardz_Middle_East&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Cardz Middle East (page does not exist)">Cardz Middle East</a>'s <a href="/w/index.php?title=Cardz_Me&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Cardz Me (page does not exist)">Cardz Me</a> - Issued to students in the Indian state of Karnataka</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Zarz%C4%85d_Transportu_Miejskiego" title="Zarząd Transportu Miejskiego">Zarząd Transportu Miejskiego</a> - uses MiFare technology (Warsaw, Poland)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/EasyRider" title="EasyRider">EasyRider</a> - uses MiFare technology (<a href="/wiki/Nottingham_City_Transport" title="Nottingham City Transport">Nottingham City Transport</a>, Nottingham, England)</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Institutions</b></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Bucknell_University" title="Bucknell University">Bucknell University</a> - integrates its student ID cards with MiFare to access main buildings and student rooms (Lewisburg, Penn)</li>
<li>New college in <a href="/wiki/Oxford" title="Oxford">Oxford</a> - uses MiFare cards for building access<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since October 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Imperial_College_London" title="Imperial College London">Imperial College London</a> - uses MiFare for staff and student ID cards to access buildings (London, UK)</li>
</ul>
